public interface UniqueObject
extends java.io.Serializable

An object with a UID created by the UIDService.

The UID is often set by a Domain Factory, and/or as a final field set in the object's constructor.

Objects that implement UniqueObject often use the UID for the "equals(Object)" and "hashCode()" methods, e.g.

   public class X implements UniqueObject .. {.. 
     public boolean equals(Object o) {
       return
         (o == this ||
         ((o instanceof X) &&
          getUID().equals(((X) o).getUID()));
     }
     public int hashCode() {
       return getUID().hashCode();
     }
   }
